# Visual language (exhibition UI)

## Before changing chrome

Read [`docs/visual-language.md`](../../docs/visual-language.md) for locked colors, type classes, spacing, grid marks, and component rules (warehouse, layer nav, L3 notes, inspector).

Target: **21.5″ iMac @ 1920×1080**. Use `rem` / site-grid units — not raw px in CSS. Shell sizes use **`VISUAL_SCALE = 1.0`** (see doc).

## After any visual change

Update **`docs/visual-language.md` in the same session**:

- Token or rule changed → edit the relevant section + add a **Changelog** entry (date, what changed).
- New SVG under `assets/ui/` → add row to **SVG assets** table.
- New component chrome → add or extend **Components** section.

Do not leave code and legend out of sync. Same discipline as `docs/CHECKPOINT.md` for physics.

## Site content

Hebrew UI strings and note data stay Hebrew — do not translate. This doc describes **chrome and typography roles**, not note body copy from the sheet.
